(La version fran=E7aise suit)

University of Quebec At Rimouski invites applications for a tenure-track
assistant professor position in Computer Science (starting: June 1st 2014).

The retained candidate will provide educational activities as part of our
computer programs, engage in research, take part in the different organisms
of the university, and where appropriate, undertake pedagogical and
administrative tasks.
Type of contract: assistant professor

Location: University of Quebec At Rimouski, Quebec, Canada

Required skills and profile:
- Ph.D in Computer Science with a bachelor of Computer Science
- Privileged areas of research specialization:
    - E-commerce and/or
- Distributed Systems and/or
 - Computer Security and/or
- Software Engineering and/or
 - Cloud Computing and/or
- Mobile computing.
 - Teaching language: French
 All qualified candidates may apply, but priority will be given to Canadian
citizens and permanent residents. We endorse the program of equal
opportunity in employment for women, visible and ethnic minorities and
natives.

Application content:

   - Letter of application
   - Curriculum vitae including the list of publications
   - References or letters of recommendation, if any

Applications should be addressed, preferably by email to
secretariat_mig@uqar.ca or sent to:
D=E9partement de math=E9matique, d'informatique et de genie, 300 all=E9e des
ursulines Rimouski, Qu=E9bec, Canada G5l3A1.

Applications should be sent no later than March 14th, 2014, at 5pm
(Montreal time).



Mehdi ADDA, Ph.D
Professeur en informatique
Directeur du module de math=E9matiques et d'informatique
D=E9partement de math=E9matiques, d'informatique et de g=E9nie
Universit=E9 du Qu=E9bec =E0 Rimouski
Tel:  (001) 418 723-1986, poste 1850, bureau K210
Fax: (001) 418 724-1879
www.uqar.ca

